<h3>ERD</h3>
 <p>
This ERD, done in rails documentation style details the relationship between datasets.
 </p>
<%= image_tag ("/assets/erd.png"), class: "img-responsive"%>

<h3>Datasets</h3>
<h4>Players</h4>
 <p>
Players will be generated by Faker and will require a full name, players will belong to teams. Players can be on multiple teams.
 </p>


<h4>Teams</h4>
 <p>
Teams will be generated by using already generated players, each team belongs to a sport league. Teams can be part of no or multiple matches. They also have a name generated by using teams.csv.
 </p>


<h4>Sports</h4>
 <p>
 A csv file contains all team names with the league they want to play in, as the file is read in the league is either found or created based on the sport name. Sports have a name generated by teams.csv.
 </p>


<h4>Locations</h4>
 <p>
Matches are played at a location in Winnipeg. City of Winnipeg open datasets were used to get names, addresses, and coordinates of various community centres and read in as a csv using Community_Centre.csv.
 </p>


<h4>Matches</h4>
 <p>
Matches need two teams in the same league to play against eachother, a location to play at, and a match date.
 </p>
